I am broadly interested and want to develop my skills within chemistry as well as improving skills related to other fields. I am eager to find a working environment which brings many motivated people together. During my free time I like to do various sports such as cycling, squash and weightlifting. I also enjoy reading literature as well as non-fiction that covers economics as well as psychology.

'company': 'University of Amsterdam', 'description': 'Group: Homogeneous, Supramolecular and Bio-inspired Catalysis
			Thesis supervisors: Joost N. H. Reek and Alexander M. Kluwer

During my PhD project I focused on the development of catalysis that can control the selectivity of substrates into value added products in collaboration with a spin off company: IncatT. I used a variety of techniques to design, synthesize and understand new catalysts and find new applications for existing supramolecular catalysts. These efforts have resulted in the selectivity control for challenging substrates such as biobased compounds.
- Publications in peer reviewed journals: 
- doi.org/10.1021/acscatal.8b00288.
- doi.org/10.1039/c9sc02558h. 
- doi.org/10.1002/cctc.201900487. 
- doi.org/10.1002/cssc.201900784. 
- doi.org/10.1002/chem.202000620.
Additional tasks:
- Teaching: Supervision of two masters projects (duration 9 months) and two bachelors projects(duration 3 months), Lab tutorial teacher (three consecutive years)
- Labchief (duration 2 years): Coordinate labordering, Manage safety issues, Ensure an effective working environment in the lab (~10 people)
